.TH DP_DESTROY_CONTEXT 3 "June 1, 2025" "libdisasterparty @DP_VERSION@" "Disaster Party Manual"

.SH NAME
dp_destroy_context \- destroy a Disaster Party LLM client context

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <disasterparty.h>
.PP
.BI "void dp_destroy_context(dp_context_t *" context ");"

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B dp_destroy_context()
function deallocates a
.BR dp_context_t
previously created by
.BR dp_init_context (3).
It frees all resources associated with the context, including the stored API key
and base URL.

After calling this function, the
.I context
pointer should not be used again. Passing a NULL pointer to this function is a
safe no-op.

.SH PARAMETERS
.TP
.B dp_context_t *\fIcontext\fP
A pointer to the Disaster Party context to be destroyed. Can be NULL.

.SH RETURN VALUE
This function does not return a value.

